trend_summary: Across the sequence, vacant parcels are steadily built over, shifting the landscape from patchy suburbs to a more continuous fabric. Warehouses and retail pads grow along arterial roads, small residential cul-de-sacs extend outward, and forest patches shrink while recreational greenery expands.
notable_changes: Expansion of warehouse/light-industrial district in the south-west corner.
New retail/commercial blocks added beside the north-central arterial corridor.
Residential cul-de-sac infill on former open lots throughout east and centre.
Noticeable reduction of contiguous forest in the north-east, partly replaced by development.
Creation or enlargement of sports fields/parkland around the central lake.
